## 1️⃣ Two Types of Forms in Django

```python
# Type 1 — Form (not tied to any model)
from django import forms

class ContactForm(forms.Form):
    name = forms.CharField(max_length=100)
    email = forms.EmailField()
    message = forms.CharField(widget=forms.Textarea)

# Type 2 — ModelForm (tied to a model)
from django import forms
from .models import Post

class PostForm(forms.ModelForm):
    class Meta:
        model = Post
        fields = ['title', 'content']
```

### When to Use Which

| Type | Use When |
|------|----------|
| `Form` | Data is **not** being saved to the database (contact form, search form, login form) |
| `ModelForm` | Data **is** being saved to the database (create post, update profile, register user) |

