## 2️⃣ How Django Processes a Form — The Full Flow

```
User fills form and clicks submit
            ↓
Browser sends POST request with form data
            ↓
Django creates form with submitted data:
form = PostForm(request.POST)
            ↓
form.is_valid() is called
            ↓
    ┌───────┴────────┐
   YES               NO
    ↓                 ↓
cleaned_data      form.errors
available         populated
    ↓                 ↓
save/process      re-render form
    ↓             with errors
redirect
```

