## 7️⃣ Widgets — Controlling How Fields Look

Widgets control the **HTML input type** rendered for each field:

```python
class PostForm(forms.ModelForm):
    class Meta:
        model = Post
        fields = ['title', 'content', 'publish_date', 'is_published']
        widgets = {
            'title': forms.TextInput(attrs={
                'class': 'form-control',
                'placeholder': 'Enter post title'
            }),
            'content': forms.Textarea(attrs={
                'class': 'form-control',
                'rows': 6
            }),
            'publish_date': forms.DateInput(attrs={
                'type': 'date',
                'class': 'form-control'
            }),
            'is_published': forms.CheckboxInput(attrs={
                'class': 'form-check-input'
            }),
        }
```

### Common Widgets

| Widget | Renders As |
|--------|------------|
| `forms.TextInput()` | `<input type="text">` |
| `forms.Textarea()` | `<textarea>` |
| `forms.EmailInput()` | `<input type="email">` |
| `forms.PasswordInput()` | `<input type="password">` |
| `forms.NumberInput()` | `<input type="number">` |
| `forms.DateInput()` | `<input type="date">` |
| `forms.CheckboxInput()` | `<input type="checkbox">` |
| `forms.Select()` | `<select>` dropdown |
| `forms.FileInput()` | `<input type="file">` |
| `forms.HiddenInput()` | `<input type="hidden">` |

